<div style="background: lightblue; font-style: italic;">
   <h2><center>Getting OneTime</center></h2>
</div>

<p style="font-size: 80%; font-style: italic; text-align: center"
>Please use OneTime <strong>1XVERSION</strong> unless you want to help
beta-test 2XVERSION.</p>

<ul>

<li><p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >GNU/Linux, Unix, Mac:</span>
    <ul style="list-style-type: circle; ">
    <li><a href="onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz" >onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz</a>
        <span style="font-style: italic;" 
              >(recommended for now, as of 2014-01-09)</span></li>
    <li><a href="onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz" >onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz</a></li>
    </ul></p>
</li>

<li><p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Windows (.zip):</span>
    <ul style="list-style-type: circle; ">
    <li><a href="onetime-1XVERSION.zip" >onetime-1XVERSION.zip</a>
        <span style="font-style: italic;" 
              >(recommended for now, as of 2014-01-09)</span></li>
    <li><a href="onetime-2XVERSION.zip" >onetime-2XVERSION.zip</a></li>
    </ul></p>
</li>

<li><p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Debian GNU/Linux:</span></p>
    <p>OneTime 1.x is packaged in <a href="http://debian.org/">Debian</a>.
    If you run the "testing" distribution of Debian or higher, do
    <tt>'sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;update&nbsp;&amp;&amp;&nbsp;sudo&nbsp;apt-get&nbsp;install&nbsp;onetime'</tt></p>
    <p style="font-style: italic;" >As of January 2014, the version of
    OneTime packaged in Debian is somewhat behind the upstream
    release.  We'll try to get Debian updated soon after OneTime 2.0
    comes out.</p></li>

<li><p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Standalone:</span></p>
    <p>Download the <a href="onetime-1XVERSION"
    >standalone 1XVERSION</a> or <a href="onetime"
    >standalone 2XVERSION</a> script directly, if you don't want the
    README, the test suite, or other incidental files.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>For access to development source code, see the <a href="dev"
>Development page</a>.</p>

